</b></i></tt></big>
<small>
<dd><a href="/crc/fw/fw-0197.html#review">Book Review</a> by Robert Huberty: The Dramas of Donorship
<p>
<dd><a href="/crc/fw/fw-1296.html#review">Book Review</a> by Robert Huberty: Defending the "The Best and the Brightest": Narcissism and Philanthropy 
 by Robert Huberty
<P>
<dd><a href="/crc/crsee/lind.html">Book Review</a> by Robert Huberty: Michael Lind's Ad Hominem Attack On Conservative Foundations
<dd><a href="/crc/crsee/hocking.html">Opinion Editorial</a> by Thomas DiLorenzo: Hocking the halo in the name of charity
<p>
<dd><a href="/crc/fw/fw-0896.html#Guilt">Book Review</a> by Robert Huberty: Money as Guilt, Philanthropy as Therapy, And The Legacy of Wealth
<p>
<dd><a href="/crc/misc/ct030696.html">Privatizing the CPB:</a> Federal Funding for the Corporation for Public Broadcasting is unnecessary and undeserved.
<p>
<dd><a href="/crc/crsee/ageop.html">Opinion Editorial</a> by CRC's President, Terry Scanlon, about the AARP
</dl>
</small>


</td>
        <td valign="top"><dl><dt><big><tt><i><b><font color="#006342">Corporate Giving</font></b></i></tt></big>
<small>
<dd>Why would corporations give billions of dollars to left-wing, anti-capitalist non-profit groups? They do, and the details are in <a href="/crc/patterns/">Patterns of Corporate Philanthropy</a>.
</dl>
</small>
  <dl><dt><big><tt><i><b><font color="#006342">Bookshelf</font>
</b></i></tt></big>
<small>
<dd><a href="/crc/books/elderly.html"><i>Frightening America's Elderly</i></a>: CRC's new book on how the Age Lobby Holds Seniors Captive
<P>
<dd><A HREF="/crc/books/green.html"><i>Environmentalism at the Crossroads</i>:</A> CRC's
 Guidebook to the Green Movement 
<P>
<dd><a href="/crc/books/nanny.html"><i>The Rise of the Nanny State</i>:</a> How consumer advocates try to run our lives.
<P>
<dd><a href="/crc/books/fulbrit.html"><i>The Fulbright Program After Fifty Years:</i></a> From mutual understanding to mutual support.
<P>
<dd><i><a href="/crc/books/pdi.html">Misdirected Giving, The Great Philanthropists and the Problem of Donor Intent</i></a>: Guidelines to prevent Philanthropists from bequeathing wealth in ways they might regret.
<P>
<dd><a href="/crc/books/neighbor.html"><i>Loving Your Neighbor</i>:</a> A collection of essays from <i>Philanthropy, Culture &amp; Society</i></a>.
<p>
<dd><a href="http://ourworld.compuserve.com/homepages/LAJarvik"><i>PBS:  Behind the Screen</i>:</a> The essential book for viewers who care about the past, present and future of public broadcasting in America.
</small>
<br>
