<!-- Generation of story text from PM publication page 8 -->

</I><BR>
Alternatives in Philanthropy<BR>
<B>Patterns of Corporate Philanthropy</B>
<P><I>(continued from page 7)</I><BR>
 liberal or left-of-center.  For their money, corporations in 1994 
supported tax-exempt groups that favor public policies that 
harm business and free enterprise.
<P>Chief among these policies was the Clinton 
health-care proposal.  Its immense and complicated bureaucracy 
